#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/util/xarray_support.py:24
#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/util/xarray_support.py:59
msgid ""
"Reads data from a file using the XArray readers and then connects the XArray "
"data to the vtkNetCDFCFREader (using zero-copy when possible). At the "
"moment, data is copied for coordinates (because they are converted to double "
"in the reader) and for certain data that is subset either in XArray or in "
"VTK.  Lazy loading in XArray is respected, that is data is accessed only "
"when it is needed. Time is passed to VTK either as an int64 for datetime64 "
"or timedelta64, or as a double (using cftime.toordinal) for cftime."
msgstr ""

