#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/util/xarray_support.py:48
msgid ""
"Returns a vtkXArrayCFReader that reads data from the XArray (using zero-copy "
"when possible). At the moment, data is copied for coordinates (because they "
"are converted to double in the reader) and for certain data that is subset "
"either in XArray or in VTK. Lazy loading in XArray is respected, that is "
"data is accessed only when it is needed. Time is passed to VTK either as an "
"int64 for datetime64 or timedelta64, or as a double (using cftime.toordinal) "
"for cftime."
msgstr ""

